                        <ln>Parker</ln>
                        <fn>Richard</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Judge</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Article asks lethargic voters to vote for judge of Court of
                Appeals.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Botts</ln>
                        <fn>John</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Article excerpts and condemns speech made by Botts to the Richmond
                    Opposition Convention in which Botts declared that any man who declares himself
                    for disunion is a Democrat.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Beautiful Consistency--Pitiable Case of an Opposition Editor</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Letcher</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Botts</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Goggin</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Asks Opposition members how they can be hoodwinked by unscrupulous leaders.
                    Article assures readers that, although Letcher used to agree on the issues of
                    slavery with Western Virginia, he now is a real friend to all the institutions
                    of the South.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Corporation Election</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Price</ln>
                        <fn>George E.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Cochran</ln>
                        <fn>George N.</fn>
                        <sf>Sr.</sf>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>All of the old officers were re-elected to the corporation, except Price,
                    who replaced Cochran.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Ratification Meeting</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>A meeting of the Democracy will take place April 16 at the Courthouse in
                    order to ratify the Harrisonburg Convention nomination.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
